column1: This tab contains a table of tourism consumption by Australian residents on outbound trips. It ranges from cell A1 to I18.
Table 6.1 Tourism consumption by Australian residents on outbound trips, purchasers' prices(a)
Total consumption by Australian residents on outbound trips ($m)
Average consumption by Australian residents on outbound trips ($)(e)
(a) Totals may not add due to rounding.
(b) Comprises consumption by outbound Australian residents within Australia before/after international trips.
(c) Outbound tourism consumption is the tourism consumption of an Australian resident outside of Australia while on an international trip.

(d) There are some conceptual differences between imports of tourism goods and services and imports of transport and travel services in the Balance of Payments and International Investment Position, Australia.
(e) Average expenditure per trip is derived based on the number of short-term resident departure trips as outlined in Overseas Arrivals and Departures, Australia.
